UnicodeStrings.StringIdContent: Choose the colors that make up your multiplayer free-for-all appearance and player emblem.
Use the D-pad to select the color you want, and then press \ue100 to set it.
The primary armor color will serve you in individual combat but will be overwritten in team scenarios. Press \ue100 to select.
The secondary armor color accents your primary color and will be overwritten in team scenarios. Press \ue100 to select.
The armor detail color preserves your individual identity in all multiplayer scenarios. Press \ue100 to select.
This color is applied to the primary icon area of your emblem. Press \ue100 to select.
This color is applied to the secondary icon area of your emblem. Press \ue100 to select.\r\n\r\nPress \ue102 to toggle on and off.
The emblem background color defines the color of the field that your icon sits on. Press \ue100 to select.
